sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant fe@{ "type": "boundary" } as Frontend
    participant API@{ "type": "control" } as API
    participant db@{ "type": "database" } as Database
    participant mq@{ "type": "queue" } as RabbitMQ (email_queue_task)
    participant mw@{ "type": "control" } as MailWorker
    participant smtp@{ "type": "boundary" } as SMTP Server

    Note over User,smtp: Phase 1 — Register

    User->>+fe: Fill register form (email, password, fullName, phone)
    fe->>+API: POST /auth/register
    API->>API: Validate body (CreateUserSchema)

    alt Validation failed
        API-->>fe: 400 Bad Request (issues)
        fe-->>User: Show field errors
    else Validation passed
        API->>+db: findUnique(user by email)
        db-->>-API: existingUser or null

        alt Email already used
            API-->>fe: 400 "Email has been used."
            fe-->>User: Show error
        else Email is new
            API->>API: bcrypt.hash(password, 10)
            API->>API: Generate mailRandomToken<br/>+ sha256(hashedVerifyToken)
            API->>+db: user.create(verifyToken = hashed)
            db-->>-API: newUser
            API->>API: jwt.sign({id, role, email})
            API->>+mq: sendToEmailQueue(verify mail with raw token link)
            mq-->>-API: Enqueued
            API-->>fe: 201 + Set-Cookie token (httpOnly, signed)
            fe-->>User: "Register successfully — check inbox"
        end
    end

    Note over mw,smtp: Phase 2 — Worker delivers verification email (async)

    mw->>+mq: consume(email_queue_task)
    mq-->>-mw: message {to, subject, html}
    mw->>+smtp: transporter.sendMail(config)
    smtp-->>-mw: 250 OK
    mw->>mq: ack(msg)

    Note over User,db: Phase 3 — User clicks verification link

    User->>+fe: Click /verify?token=<raw>
    fe->>+API: GET /auth/verify?token=...
    API->>API: hashedToken = sha256(token)
    API->>+db: findFirst(user where verifyToken = hashedToken)
    db-->>-API: user or null

    alt Token invalid / already used
        API-->>fe: 400 "Invalid or expired token."
        fe-->>User: Show error
    else Token valid
        API->>+db: user.update(verifiedAt = now, verifyToken = null)
        db-->>-API: Updated
        API-->>fe: 200 "Account is verified"
        fe-->>-User: Redirect to login / home
    end
